## Getting Started
1. Run: npm run dev-init
2. Run: npm run dev
3. Start using Tailwind classes in your .liquid files
4. See TAILWIND_EXAMPLES.md for examples

## Plugins Included
- @tailwindcss/forms           → Better form styling
- @tailwindcss/typography      → Beautiful typography defaults

## Important Configuration
- Preflight: DISABLED (preserves theme's CSS variables)
- Load order: Tailwind Components → Utilities → Original Theme CSS (last wins)
- Original theme styles take priority over Tailwind defaults
- EComposer files (ecom-*.css/js) are ignored by git

## CSS Compilation Flow
1. Tailwind Components
2. Tailwind Utilities
3. Original Theme CSS (theme.css.backup)
4. Custom @layer components/utilities
   ↓
5. Output: assets/theme.css (Original + Tailwind integrated)

## Notes
- CSS is automatically recompiled when you save changes to src/styles/theme.css
- Original theme CSS variables are preserved (e.g., var(--font-body-size))
- Custom components and utilities can be added in src/styles/theme.css using @layer
- EComposer files are managed by Shopify, not tracked in git

